20/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police have seized 455kg of hashish in two separate operations, media reported on Thursday (August 19th).
During the first, in the southeastern province of Diyarbakir, police officers confiscated 305kg of the drug and detained one person.
The remaining 150kg of hashish turned up during a police action in the southern province of Hatay.
(Anadolu news agency, Focus news agency - 19/08/10)
